cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      user-FTP process\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"         A set of functions including a protocol interpreter, a data\n";
cout<<"         transfer process and a user interface which together perform\n";
cout<<"         the function of file transfer in cooperation with one or more\n";
cout<<"         server-FTP processes.  The user interface allows a local\n";
cout<<"         language to be used in the command-reply dialogue with the\n";
cout<<"         user.\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      user-PI\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"         The user protocol interpreter initiates the control connection\n";
cout<<"         from its port U to the server-FTP process, initiates FTP\n";
cout<<"         commands, and governs the user-DTP if that process is part of\n";
cout<<"         the file transfer.\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"Postel & Reynolds                                               [Page 7]\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"                                                                        \n";
cout<<"RFC 959                                                     October 1985\n";
cout<<"File Transfer Protocol\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"   2.3.  THE FTP MODEL\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      With the above definitions in mind, the following model (shown in\n";
cout<<"      Figure 1) may be diagrammed for an FTP service.\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"                                            -------------\n";
cout<<"                                            |/---------\\|\n";
cout<<"                                            ||   User  ||    --------\n";
cout<<"                                            ||Interface|<--->| User |\n";
cout<<"                                            |\\----^----/|    --------\n";
cout<<"                  ----------                |     |     |\n";
cout<<"                  |/------\\|  FTP Commands  |/----V----\\|\n";
cout<<"                  ||Server|<---------------->|   User  ||\n";
cout<<"                  ||  PI  ||   FTP Replies  ||    PI   ||\n";
cout<<"                  |\\--^---/|                |\\----^----/|\n";
cout<<"                  |   |    |                |     |     |\n";
cout<<"      --------    |/--V---\\|      Data      |/----V----\\|    --------\n";
cout<<"      | File |<--->|Server|<---------------->|  User   |<--->| File |\n";
cout<<"      |System|    || DTP  ||   Connection   ||   DTP   ||    |System|\n";
cout<<"      --------    |\\------/|                |\\---------/|    --------\n";
cout<<"                  ----------                -------------\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"                  Server-FTP                   USER-FTP\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      NOTES: 1. The data connection may be used in either direction.\n";
cout<<"             2. The data connection need not exist all of the time.\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"                      Figure 1  Model for FTP Use\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      In the model described in Figure 1, the user-protocol interpreter\n";
cout<<"      initiates the control connection.  The control connection follows\n";
cout<<"      the Telnet protocol.  At the initiation of the user, standard FTP\n";
cout<<"      commands are generated by the user-PI and transmitted to the\n";
cout<<"      server process via the control connection.  (The user may\n";
cout<<"      establish a direct control connection to the server-FTP, from a\n";
cout<<"      TAC terminal for example, and generate standard FTP commands\n";
cout<<"      independently, bypassing the user-FTP process.) Standard replies\n";
cout<<"      are sent from the server-PI to the user-PI over the control\n";
cout<<"      connection in response to the commands.\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      The FTP commands specify the parameters for the data connection\n";
cout<<"      (data port, transfer mode, representation type, and structure) and\n";
cout<<"      the nature of file system operation (store, retrieve, append,\n";
cout<<"      delete, etc.).  The user-DTP or its designate should \"listen\" on\n";
cout<<"      the specified data port, and the server initiate the data\n";
cout<<"      connection and data transfer in accordance with the specified\n";
cout<<"      parameters.  It should be noted that the data port need not be in\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"Postel & Reynolds                                               [Page 8]\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"                                                                        \n";
cout<<"RFC 959                                                     October 1985\n";
cout<<"File Transfer Protocol\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      the same host that initiates the FTP commands via the control\n";
cout<<"      connection, but the user or the user-FTP process must ensure a\n";
cout<<"      \"listen\" on the specified data port.  It ought to also be noted\n";
cout<<"      that the data connection may be used for simultaneous sending and\n";
cout<<"      receiving.\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      In another situation a user might wish to transfer files between\n";
cout<<"      two hosts, neither of which is a local host. The user sets up\n";
cout<<"      control connections to the two servers and then arranges for a\n";
cout<<"      data connection between them.  In this manner, control information\n";
cout<<"      is passed to the user-PI but data is transferred between the\n";
cout<<"      server data transfer processes.  Following is a model of this\n";
cout<<"      server-server interaction.\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      \n";
cout<<"                    Control     ------------   Control\n";
cout<<"                    ---------->| User-FTP |<-----------\n";
cout<<"                    |          | User-PI  |           |\n";
cout<<"                    |          |   \"C\"    |           |\n";
cout<<"                    V          ------------           V\n";
cout<<"            --------------                        --------------\n";
cout<<"            | Server-FTP |   Data Connection      | Server-FTP |\n";
cout<<"            |    \"A\"     |<---------------------->|    \"B\"     |\n";
cout<<"            -------------- Port (A)      Port (B) --------------\n";
cout<<"      \n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"                                 Figure 2\n";
cout<<"\n";
cout<<"      The protocol requires that the control connections be open while\n";
cout<<"      data transfer is in progress.  It is the responsibility of the\n";
cout<<"      user to request the closing of the control connections when\n";
cout<<"      finished using the FTP service, while it is the server who takes\n";
cout<<"      the action.  The server may abort data transfer if the control\n";
cout<<"      connections are closed without command.\n";
